            <div type="textpart" subtype="section" n="First tabula" >
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><num value="10"><w lemma="δέκα">δέκα</w></num> <w lemma="ἐπί"><unclear>ἐ</unclear><supplied reason="lost">πὶ</supplied></w>
                    <lb n="2"/><num value="10"><w lemma="δέκα">δέκα</w></num>
                    <lb n="3"/><num value="100">ρ</num>
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="textpart" subtype="section" n="Second tabula" >
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><w lemma="πρό">πρὼ</w> <w lemma="δέκα">γαμε
                    <lb n="2" break="no"/><supplied reason="lost">ῖ</supplied>ν</w> <w lemma="μή">μ<unclear>ὴ</unclear></w> <w lemma="πίνω">πίνετε</w>
                    <lb n="3"/>ΗΝΗΝ
                </ab>
            </div>
            </div>
            
            <div type="apparatus">
                <div type="commentary" subtype="section" n="First tabula" >
                    <ab>The rho is written backward, buckle to the left.</ab>
                    </div> 
            <div type="translation">
                <div type="translation" subtype="section" n="First tabula" >
                    <ab>“Ten by ten, 100.”</ab>
                </div>
            <div type="translation" subtype="section" n="Second tabula" >
                <ab>“Before marrying, don’t drink . . .”</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary"> 
                <p /> 
            </div>
                <div type="commentary" subtype="section" n="Second tabula" >
                    <ab>1. Read πρό.<lb/>
                        2. The last four letters are written on the bevel to the right.<lb/>
                        We have not been able to discern the last word of this advice.</ab>
                </div>
